On the anniversary of the birth of Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the founder of Sikhism, the President sends his best wishes to those observing this occasion. He also acknowledges the contributions of Sikh Americans to the nation and highlights the importance of pluralism in America. The principles of Sikhism, such as equality, service, interfaith cooperation, and respect, are seen as shared principles by all Americans. The President encourages people to reflect on Guru Nanak's teachings on the equality of all humans and the importance of compassion in serving others.